      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was thinking to read ret back from spanner after the update is done. So that the client will not be confused if BufferWrite failed for any reason ( In this implementation they\u0027ll see a returned inv looks like the update is applied in this case, right?).\n\nBut IIUC there\u0027s a corner case for my suggestion also: we have to read the updated inv in a separated transaction, and if there\u0027s another change on the inv around the same time, the returned value may contain some changes the client doesn\u0027t make and confuse them as well?",
      "revId": "6981f3e28f023add32063fba56dfd2118c827a87",
