      "writtenOn": "2019-10-22T23:12:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the expectation is that the client checks for returned error, and if there is a returned error, ignores the returned Invocation. That protects against ambiguity/confusion, and also avoids the situation you pointed out for reading back a potentially changed invocation, which I agree would be confusing (we /could/ read it back in the same ReadWriteTransaction, actually, but that seems a little wasteful as an additional RPC if we already know the fields we want to mutate).",
